---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'How long does a typical website take to build?',
    a: 'Most projects ship in 4 to 8 weeks. The variable is content and decisions -not engineering. Sites with clear positioning and ready copy launch faster; sites that need strategy first take longer in discovery and faster after.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does "unlimited revisions" actually mean?',
    a: 'It means no revision caps inside the engagement. We iterate on design, copy, and structure until the page does its job.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Will I be able to edit the site after launch?',
    a: 'Yes. We hand over the codebase with clear conventions, and for content-heavy sections we can wire in a CMS (Sanity, Storyblok, or Astro content collections) so non-developers can edit copy without touching code.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you handle copywriting?',
    a: 'For marketing sites, yes -copy is part of conversion architecture, so we treat it as design. We work from a discovery interview, your existing materials, and your voice. You review and approve before anything ships.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What about SEO and AI search visibility?',
    a: 'Every site is built with technical SEO and Generative Engine Optimization baked in: semantic structure, schema, fast load, clean information hierarchy. If you also want ongoing organic and AI search growth, that lives under our Digital Marketing service.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can you redesign an existing site instead of starting over?',
    a: 'Sometimes. If the underlying structure is salvageable, we rebuild the front end and keep what works. If the bones are wrong -slow stack, broken funnel, fighting itself -starting fresh is faster and cheaper than retrofitting.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does it cost?',
    a: 'Marketing sites typically start in the low five figures and scale with scope. We send a fixed-fee proposal after a discovery call so you know exactly what you are paying for before we begin.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="relative bg-black py-24 text-white md:py-32">
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-grid-dark opacity-30 [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,black_30%,transparent_75%)]"></div>
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-32 top-1/3 h-96 w-96 rounded-full bg-gold/10 blur-3xl"></div>

  <div class="container-x relative">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gold-soft">
        <span class="h-px w-6 bg-gold-soft"></span>
        FAQ
      </span>
      <h2 class="mt-5 font-display text-4xl font-medium leading-[1.05] tracking-tight md:text-6xl">
        Website questions, answered.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-xl text-base text-white/65 md:text-lg">
        The things prospects ask us most before kicking off a website project.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-3xl divide-y divide-white/10 border-y border-white/10">
      {faqs.map((f) => (
        <details class="group faq-item">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-start justify-between gap-6 py-6 transition-colors hover:text-gold-soft md:py-7">
            <span class="font-display text-lg font-medium leading-snug md:text-xl">{f.q}</span>
            <span class="mt-1 flex h-7 w-7 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-white/15 text-gold-soft transition-all duration-300 group-open:rotate-45 group-open:border-gold-soft/60 group-open:bg-gold-soft/10" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" class="h-3 w-3">
                <path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="pb-6 pr-12 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/65 md:pb-7 md:text-base">{f.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-item[open] summary { color: rgb(224 198 123 / 0.95); }
</style>
